      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Problem with nLockTime is that it's hard to broadcast these transactions, so you'd have to leave your Bitcoin node running, which seems unlikely for QT users.\r\n\r\nIt might be more useful to have a way to send coins to yourself with [CheckSequenceVerify](https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Timelock#CheckSequenceVerify) such that they are locked until a certain date. Obviously with plenty of warning.",
